iomoments (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * First binary release with arch-portable build:
    - Makefile detects host multiarch triple via `gcc -print-multiarch`
      and BPF target arch via `uname -m`, replacing hardcoded x86 paths.
      Same Makefile builds on amd64 (laptop / cloud x86) and arm64
      (Raspberry Pi 5, AWS Graviton).
    - Two binary packages produced: amd64 (host: Ubuntu 24.04) and
      arm64 (host: Debian 13). Both built natively per arch.
  * No userspace API or runtime-behavior changes from 0.1.0.

 -- Ed Hodapp <ed@hodapp.com>  Mon, 04 May 2026 14:00:00 +0000

iomoments (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian/Ubuntu binary package.
  * Userspace collector + BPF programs (k=4 default, k=3 fallback for
    kernels >= 6.17 where the k=4 verifier budget is exceeded).
  * Self-resolving BPF object lookup via /proc/self/exe — same binary
    works in-tree (build/iomoments + build/*.bpf.o siblings) and after
    install (/usr/bin/iomoments + /usr/lib/iomoments/*.bpf.o).
  * FHS layout: binary in /usr/bin, BPF objects in /usr/lib/iomoments/.

 -- Ed Hodapp <ed@hodapp.com>  Mon, 04 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
